Considerations for Selecting Related Attributes

There’s a direct relationship with the DMO, related attributes, and the filters you can apply.

NOTE For engagement data, activation supports a 90-day lookback window. If related attributes are selected for an activation with a rapid segment publish, the lookback window is seven days. Activation considers engagement data within this window, and any records outside of this window aren't considered when selecting your output values.

When selecting related attributes, consider these guidelines:

Related attributes support choosing DMOs from one path. If a DMO has a Direct path and Related path, choose one to use. If there are multiple paths available, select the path with the relevant DMOs you want to activate. For example: If you want to activate attributes from Policy Accounts and Policy Details, select path 1 and path 2 is unavailable to select.
Filters apply on your DMOs. Attributes can only be used as filters if they belong to a DMO that’s being activated. For example: If path 1 is selected and all of the DMOs are being activated, you can select any of the attributes from that path as a filter. Any attributes from path 2 can’t be used as a filter.
Inherited filters allow you to apply filters from your parent DMO to all the child DMOs. For example: If you apply a filter on Insurance Policy, it applies to all the attributes selected from Policy Products, Policy Accounts, and Policy Details. If you apply a filter on Policy Products, only Policy Accounts and Policy Details inherit this filter.
You can select up to 20 related attributes per activation. For example: You’re able to select 9 attribute values from Insurance Policy and 11 attribute values from Policy Products.
You can use up to 100 activations with related attributes. After reaching that limit, you can choose to delete related attributes from existing activations, delete unused activations, or create activations with only direct attributes.
The segment size is checked at the time of activation. If the segment has more than 10 million records and contains related attributes when you publish, the segment doesn’t activate.
The segmentation and activation attribute libraries achieve different purposes so they behave differently. In segmentation, the entire DMO hierarchy is displayed. In activation, the DMOs that are one hop away from the object are displayed. To get to other DMOs, click through the hierarchy.
Activation doesn’t automatically acquire segmentation filters. To activate specific values for your attribute, apply filters to your activation. Use segmentation filters to find users who qualify for the segment. Use activation filters to find attributes for message personalization.
